  </header>
  
  <body>

<p> Generates the &lt;body&gt; element for the page, and is involved in generating and organizing the JavaScript on
  the page. You should always use the Body component for your &lt;body&gt; tag, since you can never
  know which components within the page will require the services it provides.
</p>

<p>
  <strong>See also: <link href="&apiroot;/html/Body.html">org.apache.tapestry.html.Body</link>, &Rollover;, &Script;</strong> 
</p>

